  <refnamediv>
    <refname>scidoe_simplelinreg</refname><refpurpose>Univariate linear regression</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>



<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   H = scidoe_simplelinreg(X,Y)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>H :</term>
      <listitem><para> a 1-by-2 matrix of doubles, where a=H(1) is the slope and b=H(2) is the intercept</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function fits data in linear model y=a*x+b,
where a is the slope and b is the y-intercept.
   </para>
   <para>
The coefficients a and b are so that they
are the best fit of the data in the least squares sense.
   </para>
   <para>
We use Scilab's backslash operator, which uses Gaussian Elimination,
making it faster than using x = inv(A)*B.
   </para>
   <para>
Our system should be overdetermined, meaning having more
equations than unknowns, otherwise the system doesn't have a solution.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

